<subSubSection id="48D355CA8EA9FF2848A750F6FE0CFE3F" lastPageId="232" lastPageNumber="233" pageId="231" pageNumber="232" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418EA9FF2848A750F6FE05FE5C" blockId="231.[151,1436,2010,2035]" lastBlockId="232.[151,1437,151,608]" lastPageId="232" lastPageNumber="233" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538EA9FF2748A750F6FE34F803" bold="true" box="[151,401,2010,2035]" pageId="231" pageNumber="232">Description of Male.</emphasis>
Fully winged; length 
<quantity id="C731ABA48EA9FF274A9150F6FD58F802" box="[673,765,2010,2034]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9" pageId="231" pageNumber="232" unit="mm" value="2.9">2.9 mm</quantity>
. Head black, except mandible testaceous; antenna brown; mesosoma and metasoma black; legs brown, except tarsi and protibia testaceous. Antenna filiform; antennal segments in following proportions: 8:6:6:6:6:6:5.5:5.5:5:8. Head dull, completely reticulate rugose; frontal line complete; occipital carina complete; POL = 5.5; OL = 3.5; OOL = 7; OPL = 6; TL = 5. Scutum dull, reticulate rugose. Notauli absent. Scutellum shiny, punctate, unsculptured among punctures, except posterior third reticulate rugose. Metanotum dull, reticulate rugose. Propodeum reticulate rugose, without lateral pointed apophyses; dorsal surface with very wide areolae; posterior surface with tracks of two longitudinal keels. Fore wing hyaline, without dark transverse bands; stigmal vein curved (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48EA6FF284AA15643FCA5FE77" box="[657,768,367,391]" captionStart="PLATE 65" captionStartId="224.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[222,1389,239,1814]" captionTargetId="figure-78@224.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="224" captionText="PLATE 65. A, E. Chelae, holotypes. B, C. Stigmal veins. D. Male genitalia, holotype. A. Bocchus haladai (from Olmi 2008b). B, D. B. indicus, male (from Olmi 1987a). C, E. B. laotianus, female (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.18 mm for A, 0.35 mm for B and C, 0.23 mm for D and 0.18 mm for E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278601" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278601/files/figure.png" pageId="232" pageNumber="233">Plate 65B</figureCitation>
); marginal cell open. Petiole very short. Genitalia in plate 65D. Tibial spurs 1/1/2.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418EA6FF2848F75694FE0CFE3F" blockId="232.[151,1437,151,608]" box="[199,425,439,464]" pageId="232" pageNumber="233">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538EA6FF2848F75694FE80FE20" bold="true" box="[199,293,440,464]" pageId="232" pageNumber="233">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
